A more bland potatoes au gratin I've never tasted. Even the blue cheese didn't do much to liven it up. Interesting, though, how the cream "becomes" a lovely, smooth sauce when boiled away at 425 degrees for 25 minutes. Easy to construct? Yes! Delicious? Not for me. If I ever do make this again, I'll add more spices for some zip. As the recipe is written, these potatoes are barely breathing.

